prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "The system allows users to choose between using the service center side or the car owner side.",
      "evidence_quote": "A person starts by choosing whether they are using the service center side or the car owner side."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Service center users can register or log in if already registered.",
      "evidence_quote": "If they are a service center, they can either register or log in if already registered."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "After logging in, service center users can enter damaged parts, update parts information, or send expiry-related notifications.",
      "evidence_quote": "After logging in, they reach their home area where they can enter damaged parts, update parts information, or send expiry-related notifications."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Service center users can log out after finishing any of the above activities.",
      "evidence_quote": "After finishing any of these, they can continue using the system or log out."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Car owner users can register or log in.",
      "evidence_quote": "If they are a car owner, they can also register or log in."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "After logging in, car owners can view parts information, request or respond to services, or report a service center.",
      "evidence_quote": "After logging in, they reach their home area where they can view parts information, request or respond to services, or report a service center."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Car owners can select required parts and make a payment when choosing a service.",
      "evidence_quote": "If they choose a service, they can select the required parts and make a payment, and then continue."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Car owners can log out after completing their activities.",
      "evidence_quote": "After completing their activities, they can log out, and it ends."
    }
  ]
}

